<h3>Who can help?</h3>
The BibleTime development team is very small. We are always looking for new developers, translators and docwriters. We are looking for people who are
<ol>
 <LI>willing to learn</li>
 <LI>willing to contribute over a longer period of time (not just a week)</li>
 <LI>not perfect ;)</li>
 <LI>It would be great if you have programming knowledge;
if you don't, you can still help with the translations and the artwork.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Follow these steps to get started with development</h3>
<ol>
<li><b>Subscribe to development mailinglist</b>
<p>Depending on your browser software this link could work:
<A HREF="mailto:majordomo@crosswire.org?&body=subscribe bt-devel">majordomo@crosswire.org</A> If it doesn't, send a message with empty subject and the body containing <TT>subscribe bt-devel</TT> to <A HREF="mailto:majordomo@crosswire.org">majordomo@crosswire.org</A>.
After you subscribed successfully you can send an eMail to the development mailinglist using
<A HREF="mailto:bt-devel@crosswire.org">bt-devel@crosswire.org</A>.
</p></li><br>

<li><b>Get the sources</b>
<p>We use CVS to share the development sources with other developers. If you want to join our team register at <A HREF="http://www.sourceforge.net/">sourceforge</A>
and send us your username. After we added you to our project as a developer you have write access to our repository.<BR>
If you simply want to use the current development version you have to use anonymous CVS.</p>

<P>See the <A HREF="http://sourceforge.net/cvs/?group_id=954">CVS instructions</A>. A web <A HREF="http://cvs.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/cvsweb.cgi?cvsroot=bibletime">web interface to the cvs</A> is available.
</P></li><br>

<li><b>Read the docs</b>
<p>Please read all of the <A HREF="http://sourceforge.net/docman/index.php?group_id=954"> BibleTime documentation</A>, not only the development related stuff.Also there is a handbook in the cvs repository (<A
HREF=http://cvs.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/viewcvs.cgi/~checkout~/bibletime/bibletime/bibletime/docs/en/HTML/index.html?content-type=text/html>online version</A>)
as well as a class documentation (<A HREF=http://cvs.sourceforge.net/cgi-bin/viewcvs.cgi/~checkout~/bibletime/bibletime/bibletime-api/html/index.html?content-type=text/html>online version</A>).<br>
Don't be shy, ask on the mailinglist if you have questions. We're happy you want to help!
</p></li><br>

<li><b>Get some task(s) to do</b>
<p>Browse to our <A HREF="http://sourceforge.net/pm/?group_id=954">taskmanager</A> on sourceforge and choose some jobs.
</p></li><br></ol>
